name: pepper steak
instructions:
1. Cut meat in half lengthwise with a sharp knife, then crosswise into thin slices. 

2. Slice green peppers and onions. 

3. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.

4. Brown meat in hot oil, then add peppers and onions; cook 1 to 2 minutes. 

5. Stir in water and garlic powder. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

6. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

7. Shred carrots.

8. Serve on a bed of shredded carrots.
